<http://identifiers.org/mgi/MGI:107435>
        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2954  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Cadherin-9 Mediates Trans-cellular Adhesion via Cadherins-6 and -10\"\nCell aggregation assay:\n-\"To determine whether cadherin-9 can bind in trans to other cadherins expressed in the hippocampus, we conducted cell aggregation assays (Takeichi and Nakagawa, 2001).\"...\"we identified four heterophilic cadherin pairs; cadherins-6/9, -9/10, -10/6, and -8/11 (Figures S4C and S4D).\"\n- \"We then expressed Cdh9-smFPFLAG in one set of CHO cells to simulate CA3 neurons and plated them with a second set of CHO cells expressing Cdh6-smFPHA, Cdh10-smFPMYC, or Cdh6-smFPHA and Cdh10-smFPMYC (Figure 4C) to simulate CA1 neurons. Immunostaining shows that cadherins localize at the interaction interfaces in all combinations tested (Figures 4C and S4E).\"\n- \"All cadherins tested were enriched in the synaptosome fraction relative to lysates by P14 (Figures 4E). \"\n- \"We co-cultured neurons expressing Cdh9-smFPFLAG with neurons expressing Cdh6-smFPHA, Cdh10-smFPMYC, or both Cdh6-smFPHA and Cdh10-smFPMYC and immunostained for epitope tags and the synaptic markers vGLUT1 and PSD95. We observed co-localization of every pairwise combination of cadherins at synapses (Figures 4G-4I). \"...\"all three cadherins simultaneously co-localize at synaptic sites marked by juxtaposed vGLUT and PSD95 puncta (Figure 4J).\"\n\nIn Fig.2 and 5 the in situ consequence of the adhesion activity for the Cadherin-6/9/10 is shown via effects on spine morphology and LTP (not annotated).. Experimental description: - Overexpression constructs: Cdh6 (mouse), Cdh9 (presumed mouse), Cdh10 (mouse)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2954" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

